{
  "texts": [
    "According to Mhasakar et al. 's interview conducted on participants, sometimes they doubt that the reflection from AI is wrong, and a more transparent speaking score-calculating process is needed [7].",
    "Likewise, Algaraady and Mahyoob indicated ChatGPT's behavior of making up mistakes when the original text was correct [13].",
    "These show the deficiency of applying current LLMs to EFL learning and emphasize the value of enhancing their accuracy.",
    "Due to the overall good performances of LLMs in EFL education, training EFL educators to teach and supervise students' usages of AIs is also important, because they need to avoid EFL learners being misled by LLMs.Furthermore, to confirm the future research and development directions of applying LLMs in EFL education, the research gaps and limitations of reviewed papers should also be identified.Whether in the speaking or writing education field, the sampling range of these studies is limited to only a few countries, which leads to an unbalanced situation in that most of the learners have the same native language.",
    "Specifically, among these 9 studies, 6 of them sampled students whose native language is Chinese [8][9][10][11][12][13], two did not specify students' native languages [12,13], and only one specified that their samples have 8 different native languages [7]."
  ]
}